Node.js E2 Assignment:

Assignment Objectives
. Build a web application using Node.js, Express, EJS, Socket.io, Rest Apis, Microservices
. Implement user authentication, user management, and CRUD (Create, Read, Update, Delete) operations for users.

Assignment Details

1. Login Page (Landing Page)
   Using EJS, create a Login Page with:
   Fields
   . Email ID
   . Password
   Requirements
   . Validate credentials asynchronously
   . On successful login -> Redirect to User List Page.
   . On failure -> Show error message.
   Security Requirements
   . Store passwords hashed (bcrypt recommended).
   . Prevent unauthorized access to all internal routes via sessions/JWT.

   PAGE DONE ( login.ejs )

2. User List Page
   Accessible only after user authentication.
   Display
   A table showing:
   . Name
   . Email
   . Birthdate
   . Profile Photo
   . Role (SuperAdmin / ViewAdmin / EditAdmin)
   Role-Based Access
   . SuperAdmin -> Full access
   . EditAdmin - Edit only
   . ViewAdmin -> View only
   Real-Time Update (Socket.IO Requirement)
   . Notify all connected users when a new user is created/updated/deleted.

3. Create User Page
   User Form should include:
   . Name
   . Email (must be unique)
   . Password
   . Birthdate
   . User Photo (upload)
   . User Role
   Requirements
   . Handle file upload asynchronously using fs module.
   . Store user details in JSON file or DB.
   . After successful creation - Redirect to User List Page.

   PAGE ALMOST DONE ( user-form.ejs ) --> file upload pending ...
   http://localhost:3000/user-form && http://localhost:3000/create-user

4. Edit User Page
   Editable fields:
   . Name
   . Password
   . User Photo
   Requirements
   . Update data asynchronously.
   . Refresh User List after update.

5. Delete User
   . Implement delete function (REST API DELETE or server-side route).
   . Perform deletion asynchronously.
   . Update user list and notify via Socket.IO.

Additional Requirements

1. Use Express for backend routing and server handling.
2. Use EJS as the template engine for dynamic HTML rendering.
3. Implement basic validation for all input fields.
4. Use a temporary in-memory data store (e.g., JSON file) to manage users. (Optional: Use a database for persistence.)
5. Ensure proper error handling and feedback for each action (e.g., success and failure messages).
   You must perform at least the following using the Node.js File System:
6. Store all users in users.json (if not using DB).
7. Store uploaded images in an /uploads folder.
8. You must use: async/await, Promises, Non-blocking FS operations in all CRUD operations.
9. Create a separate REST API (Express Router or separate microservice):

Endpoints:

1. GET /api/users
2. GET /api/users/:id
3. POST /api/users
4. PUT /api/users/:id
5. DELETE /api/users/:id
6. Split the application into at least 2 services:
7. Authentication Service
8. Login
9. JWT/Session
10. User Management Service
11. CRUD Operations
12. REST API Endpoints

Optional Enhancements

1. Implement client-side validation for forms using JavaScript.
2. Add CSS for better UI/UX.

